modules.description: Converts text between different character encodings using GNU libiconv. Handles strings and byte sequences in various encodings such as UTF-8, ISO-8859-1, and Windows-1252. Translates email headers from Latin-1 to UTF-8 for proper display in modern systems.

Converts strings between different character encodings using a low-level converter handle. Operates on strings and maintains a converter state for efficient repeated conversions. Handles tasks like transforming UTF-8 to ISO-8859-1 or GBK to UTF-16 in text processing pipelines.
